BT /F1 11 Tf 54 730 Td (#### Step 2: Fetch historical weather) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 707 Td (`get_weather_data\(req.lat, req.lon, location_name=req.district\)` fetches daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 692 Td (weather history.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 669 Td (If no weather data is returned, the function raises `404`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 646 Td (#### Step 3: Convert daily weather into monthly features) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 623 Td (`engineer_features\(weather_df\)` groups daily weather into month-level rows.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 600 Td (This is needed because crop recommendation is done on monthly climate patterns,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 585 Td (not raw daily rows.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 562 Td (#### Step 4: Find the requested month and year) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 539 Td (The code first tries:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 516 Td (- exact `year` and `month`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 493 Td (If that is not found, it falls back to:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 470 Td (- matching only `month`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 447 Td (This makes the route more flexible when exact year data is missing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 424 Td (#### Step 5: Get soil context) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 401 Td (`get_soil_context\(req.lat, req.lon\)` returns soil properties for the location.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 378 Td (Then user-provided values can override the fetched soil values:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 355 Td (- `soil_type`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 340 Td (- `soil_ph`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 325 Td (- `organic_matter_pct`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 310 Td (- `irrigation_level`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 287 Td (#### Step 6: Predict crops) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 264 Td (`predict_crops\(weather_dict, soil_context=soil_context, state=state\)` returns) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 249 Td (ranked crops.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 226 Td (The result is sorted by confidence.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
