BT /F2 14 Tf 54 581 Td (13. Interview-Ready Explanation) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 553 Td (If someone asks you to explain this backend in simple terms, you can say:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 530 Td (> AgriSense backend is a FastAPI-based agriculture recommendation system. It) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 515 Td (fetches weather and soil data for a given location, converts daily weather into) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 500 Td (monthly features, uses crop knowledge from JSON files, and predicts suitable) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 485 Td (crops with a trained XGBoost model. If the model or live APIs fail, it has) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 470 Td (fallback logic so the system still provides useful answers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 447 Td (If they ask about ML specifically:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 424 Td (> The ML model is trained on engineered climate, soil, and crop-economic) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 409 Td (features. The labels are created using agronomic rule logic, so the model learns) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 394 Td (to reproduce those suitability rules. The backend saves the trained model with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 379 Td (Joblib and uses it later for fast predictions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 356 Td (If they ask about explainability:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 333 Td (> Each recommendation includes a confidence score, reason, growth instructions,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 318 Td (and regional context, so the system is easier to trust and explain.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 295 Td (---) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 268 Td (14. Limitations and Improvement Ideas) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 240 Td (This section is useful for interviews because it shows that you understand the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 225 Td (project critically.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 202 Td (14.1 Current limitations) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 178 Td (- The ML labels are rule-generated, not based on real field outcomes) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 163 Td (- Weather requests still depend on an external API) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
